Remarks

Adults of this species are similar to those of
T. turcicus Ayy
₁ ld ₁ z &
Doğan, 2003
in the appearnnce of idiosoma and having the same chaetotaxy on the legs, but can be separated from the latter by having peritremes with one loop (vs: 3 loops), palptarsus with 1 eupathidium (vs: 2 eupathidia).
Etymology
The specific name refers to the occurrence of this species in Australia .
